  "body": "Hello all!\r\n\r\nFor my compiler app, I am trying to use the '@remix-project/remix-solidity' package. \r\n\r\nIt is working like a charm in a simple create-react-app environment, but not working at all in my next.js setup - with the exact same code.\r\n\r\nI am using the following approach:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport {\r\n\tbaseURLBin,\r\n\tcompile,\r\n\tCompiledContract,\r\n\tCompilerAbstract,\r\n\tpathToURL,\r\n} from '@remix-project/remix-solidity';\r\n\r\n// Extract and set the compiler version path\r\n\t\tconst compilerVersion = getCompilerVersionFromSolidityCode(codeToCompile, compilerVersions);\r\n\r\n\t\tif (compilerVersion) {\r\n\t\t\t(pathToURL as any)[compilerVersion] = baseURLBin;\r\n\t\t\tconsole.log('Updated pathToURL: ', pathToURL);\r\n\t\t\tsetSelectedCompilerVersion(compilerVersion);\r\n\t\t} else {\r\n\t\t\t...\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\tconsole.log('Compiler version path detected:', compilerVersion);\r\n\r\n\t\tconst compilerResponse = (await compile(\r\n\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\t[CONTRACT_FILE_NAME]: {\r\n\t\t\t\t\tcontent: codeToCompile,\r\n\t\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\tversion: selectedCompilerVersion,\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\r\n\t\t\tresolveNpmImports\r\n\t\t)) as CompilerAbstract;\r\n\r\n\t\tdebugConsole.log('Compiler response: ', compilerResponse);\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is working perfectly fine in the CRA setup, I receive these logs: \r\n\r\n```\r\ngetCompilerVersionFromSolidityCode: Matching compiler version found: soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js\r\nindex.tsx:180 Updated pathToURL:  {soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js: 'https://binaries.soliditylang.org/bin'}\r\nindex.tsx:192 Compiler version path detected: soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js\r\ncompiler.ts:208 Loading https://binaries.soliditylang.org/bin/soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js with worker\r\n// proper compiler result is logged\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut in my next.js setup, I get this: \r\n\r\n```\r\ngetCompilerVersionFromSolidityCode: Matching compiler version found: soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js\r\nUpdated pathToURL:  {soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js: 'https://binaries.soliditylang.org/bin'}\r\ndebug.ts:4 Compiler version path detected: soljson-v0.8.23+commit.f704f362.js\r\nContractDeployer.tsx:330 Loading undefined/soljson-v.js with worker\r\ndebug.ts:4 Compiler response:  {\r\n    \"languageversion\": \"\",\r\n    \"data\": {\r\n        \"error\": {\r\n            \"formattedMessage\": \"Worker error: Uncaught NetworkError: Failed to execute 'importScripts' on 'WorkerGlobalScope': The script at 'http://localhost:3000/_next/static/chunks/undefined/soljson-v.js' failed to load.\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n \r\nThe log \"Loading ... with worker\" comes from within the '@remix-project/remix-solidity' package - apparently the URL to load the compiler binary can't be constructed in the Next.js setting. \r\n\r\nQuestion:\r\n\r\nCould somebody tell me if there is anything specific I need to consider when using the package in a Next.js environment compare to a CRA environment? \r\n\r\nThank you very much in advance! Every help is appreciated.\r\n  ",
